@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}
<link href="/css/home.css" rel="stylesheet" />
<main>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <div class="text-center mt-5">
                    <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to News Classifier</h1>
                    <p class="lead">We provide services for detecting online articles containing anti-government content. Additionally, we offer various features including data crawling from articles, YouTube comments, automatic responses to negative comments, and more.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row justify-content-center mt-5">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Our Technologies</h2>
                <div class="card shadow-lg">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Machine Learning - Naive Bayes Model</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">We utilize advanced machine learning algorithms, specifically the Naive Bayes model, to analyze and classify online articles, comments, and other text-based data.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card shadow-lg mt-4">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Web Crawling</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Our web crawling technology enables us to collect data from various online sources, including news websites and social media platforms.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card shadow-lg mt-4">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Natural Language Processing (NLP)</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Using NLP techniques, we process and understand the semantic meaning of text, allowing us to detect nuanced patterns and sentiments.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card shadow-lg mt-4">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Backend Technologies</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Our main functionalities are implemented by calling APIs on the backend, which are written in C#. </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card shadow-lg mt-4">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Frontend Technologies</h5>
                        <p class="card-text"> We utilize Bootstrap 5 for frontend design.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card shadow-lg mt-4">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Database Technologies</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Our database is powered by Microsoft SQL Server, hosted on a dedicated server. Additionally, user activities are logged to provide a history of their interactions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>

<style>
    .or-divider {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #6c757d; /* Màu xám */
    }
</style>
<div class="row justify-content-center mt-5">
    <div class="col-md-8">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">MVC Architecture</h2>
        <div class="card shadow-lg">
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="card-text">MVC (Model-View-Controller) is an architectural pattern commonly used in web development. It separates an application into three main components:</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img id="mvc-image" class="sliding-image" alt="MVC Architecture" width="400" height="200">
                </div>
                <p class="card-text mt-3">This separation of concerns allows for better organization, maintainability, and testability of the codebase.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    var images = ["/img/mvc.png", "/img/mvc-api.png"];
    var currentIndex = 0;
    function changeImage() {
        currentIndex = (currentIndex + 1) % images.length;
        document.getElementById("mvc-image").src = images[currentIndex];
    }
    setInterval(changeImage, 2000);
</script>



